snippet.textDisplay: Playing Tu Jhoom in the Sethi havelis of Peshawar is breathtaking! This is called the Sethi house; one of the remaining havelis of 12 constructed by the Sethi merchants of Peshawar between approx 1810 to 1920s. This haveli was bought by the Dept of Archeology around 2005/2006 and named the Sethi House. It was originally the zenan-khana of the larger Karim Buksh Sethi haveli. ❤

snippet.textDisplay: Coke Studio Pakistan has managed to capture the soul of the nation through its music. Each composition is a masterpiece, a harmonious blend of tradition and modernity. The artists have breathed life into timeless melodies, creating a soundscape that is both deeply rooted and incredibly fresh. The production quality is unparalleled, making every listen an immersive auditory experience. Coke Studio Pakistan is undoubtedly a treasure trove of musical brilliance.
